44
00:03:24,149 --> 00:03:27,639
They forced me to drink, laughed at me, and scolded me. But none of these made me feel so upset.

45
00:03:27,639 --> 00:03:31,039
But why am I so upset when I just spoke out what I always wanted to tell them?

46
00:03:31,039 --> 00:03:33,850
I feel bad. I'm such a coward!

47
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:38,909
Miss He. Do I deserve to be pushed aside and isolated?

48
00:03:38,909 --> 00:03:44,119
So somehow you feel guilty when what you did was speak out the truth to protect yourself.

49
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:05,549
If speaking out your inner thoughts is the best way to protect yourself,

50
00:04:05,549 --> 00:04:11,220
but you feel that your sense of security should not be built on hurting other people.

51
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:13,010
Hey.

52
00:04:13,010 --> 00:04:16,129
You abided by the rules during the exam

53
00:04:16,129 --> 00:04:19,360
and successfully prevented us from going astray.

54
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,590
To show our gratitude we bought you a white rabbit toffee.

55
00:04:21,590 --> 00:04:22,659
It's okay. I don't need it.

56
00:04:22,659 --> 00:04:24,620
Just take it!

57
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:25,569
Open it.

58
00:04:25,569 --> 00:04:27,570
Hurry up!

59
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:31,040
It's sweet. Taste it.

60
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,249
Eat it!

61
00:04:32,249 --> 00:04:35,200
I'll tell the teacher if you guys don't stop.

62
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:45,560
Xiao Mo. How do you feel when you think of that classmate now?

63
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,850
I feel guilty.

64
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:50,390
I hate myself.

65
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:54,239
